OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F418A1738249282
OL,3,CThames Valley Police Chief Constable
OL,4,Creinstated following suspension
OL,6,F"I was clear at the time that the
OL,7,Fsuspension was a neutral act, and I
OL,8,Freiterate that same point now. The
OL,9,FChief Constable, as with all of us, is
OL,10,Finnocent unless proven otherwise, and
OL,11,Fit remains for the IOPC to conclude
OL,12,Ftheir investigation and I once again
OL,13,Furge them to conclude it as quickly as
OL,14,Fpossible.
OL,16,F"I have spoken to the Policing
OL,17,FMinister about the implications for
OL,18,Fthe Police Accountability Review and
OL,19,Fhow the Government should clarify the
OL,20,Fpowers of PCCs when acting in the
OL,21,Fwider public interest in such cases.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
